
Chessboard
==========

On this notebook tutorial we present a example to create
phenomenal.Chessboard Object.

1. Prerequisites
----------------

1.1 Download data Set
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Download the chessboard image dataset
`here <https://gforge.inria.fr/frs/download.php/file/35019/CHESSBOARD_PhenoArch_2013_sv_face1.zip>`__
and extract it.

Indicate the path in **data\_path\_directory** variable below.

.. code:: python

    data_path_directory = './CHESSBOARD_PhenoArch_2013_sv_face1/'

1.2 Load path file
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

.. code:: python

    import glob
    
    # Load path files from directory
    files_path = glob.glob(data_path_directory + '*.png')
    
    # Extract angles from path files
    angles = map(lambda x: int((x.split('_sv')[-1]).split('.png')[0]), files_path)
    
    images_path = dict()
    for i in range(len(files_path)):
        images_path[angles[i]] = files_path[i]

1.3 Display a image
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

.. code:: python

    %matplotlib notebook
    
    import matplotlib.pyplot
    from cv2 import imread, cvtColor, IMREAD_COLOR, COLOR_RGB2BGR
    
    
    def show_image(image):
        image = cvtColor(image, COLOR_RGB2BGR)
        matplotlib.pyplot.imshow(image)
    
    
    angle = 90
    image = imread(images_path[angle], IMREAD_COLOR)
    show_image(image)

2. Chessboard object
--------------------

2.1 Create
~~~~~~~~~~

Create chessboard object with square size and shape of chessboard

.. code:: python

    import alinea.phenomenal.chessboard
    
    square_size_of_chessboard = 47 # In mm
    square_shape_of_chessboard = (8, 6) # (8 square x 6 square on chessboard)
    
    # BUILD CHESSBOARD OBJECT
    chessboard = alinea.phenomenal.chessboard.Chessboard(
        square_size_of_chessboard, square_shape_of_chessboard)
    
    # DISPLAY IT
    print chessboard


.. parsed-literal::

    Chessboard Attributes :
    Square size (mm): 47
    Shape : (8, 6)
    Number of angle : 0
    
    

2.2 Find corners
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

.. code:: python

    from cv2 import imread, IMREAD_GRAYSCALE
    
    # LOAD IMAGE AND FIND CHESSBOARD CORNERS IN EACH IMAGE
    for angle in images_path:
        # LOAD IMAGE WITH OPENCV
        img = imread(images_path[angle], IMREAD_GRAYSCALE)
        # CALL CHESSBOARD FUNCTION FOR FIND CORNERS
        chessboard.find_and_add_corners(angle, img, verbose=True)
        
    # DISPLAY IT
    print chessboard

2.4 Display it
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

.. code:: python

    from cv2 import imread, IMREAD_COLOR
    
    # LOAD IMAGE RGB
    angle = 90
    img = imread(images_path[angle], IMREAD_COLOR)
     
    # DRAW RED POINT ON IMAGE CORNERS POSITION
    points_2d = chessboard.corners_points[angle].astype(int)
    img[points_2d[:, 0, 1], points_2d[:, 0, 0]] = [0, 0, 255]
    # DISPLAY IT
    show_image(img)
